headline.main: LITTLE SIGN OF FOE SEEN IN NEW GUINEA; Fliers Bombing Trail to Buna Fail to Find Even a Curl of Smoke From a Camp AUSTRALIANS PUSHING ON Cautious Despite Reports, They Prepare Against Trap by Clearing Their Flanks

lead_paragraph: AT UNITED NATIONS HEADQUARTERS, Australia, Friday, Oct. 2 (AP) -- Allied troops are continuing to make progress in the Owen Stanley mountain area of New Guinea, without meeting any Japanese opposition, the Allied command reported today.
